---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Divider from '../components/Divider.astro';
import SocialMedia from '../components/SocialMedia.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { SECTIONS, TECH_STACK, SOCIAL_MEDIA } from '../consts'; 

import leetcodeImage from '../assets/about/leetcode.webp';
import studysession from '../assets/about/studysession.webp';
import gardenharvest from '../assets/about/radish.webp';

const currentLanguages = Object.values(TECH_STACK.CURRENT).filter(lang => lang !== "Rust");
const futureLanguages = Object.values(TECH_STACK.FUTURE);
---

<MainLayout title="But, Who Am I?" subtitle="what do I do in my day-to-day? why is there a crab at the top?">
  <section class="about-content">
      <div class="social-media">
        <p>These are my 'social media':</p>
        <SocialMedia />
      </div>

      <Divider />

      <section class="bio">
        <p>
          Well, my (real) name is <strong>Carlos</strong>,
          but you can call me <strong>Aru</strong> (ngl, I really like it!).
        </p>

        <p>
          I'm a 22-year-old <strong>Computer Science</strong> student, and
          that's the reason why I'm really into everything about
          low-level programming; I fell in love with how things work under the
          hood.
        </p>

        <p>
          My favorite language is <strong data-lang="Rust">Rust</strong>, and as
          you can imagine, that's the reason for that cute, tiny, eye-catching
          crab moving side to side at the top of the page. Although, I usually
          program in:
        </p>

        <div class="lang-row">
          {currentLanguages.map((lang) => (
          <span class="lang-text" data-lang={lang}>{lang}</span>
          ))}
        </div>

        <p>Also, I'd like to learn:</p>

        <div class="lang-row">
          {futureLanguages.map((lang) => (
          <span class="lang-text" data-lang={lang}>{lang}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>
    
      <Divider />

      <section class="activity-log">
        <p>
          <strong>In November 2024</strong> I decided to create an
          X/Twitter account with the main purpose of sharing my CS life.
          I quickly found a friendly community called
          <strong>"Study Buddy"</strong> where lots of people
          share their personal <strong>notes</strong>,
          <strong>study-session POV</strong>,
          <strong>setups</strong>, and several other
          <strong>aesthetic things</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          For instance, this is my usual view when <strong>I'm studying at home</strong>. It looks nice, doesn't it?
        </p>

        <figure class="display-box">
          <Image src={studysession} alt="CS study session" />
          <figcaption>Home study environment.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <section class="activity-log">
        <p class="logical-problems">
          One of the things I enjoy the most is solving logic problems. I'm
          sure you're familiar with platforms like{" "}
          <strong data-site="LeetCode">LeetCode</strong> (my favorite btw ☝🏽🤓),{" "}
          <strong>HackerRank</strong>,
          <strong>CodeSignal</strong>,
          <strong>CodeForces</strong>, and so on. I spend
          around 2 hours a day solving these kinds of problems.
        </p>

        <p>If you want to check out my profile, here's my LeetCode:</p>

        <figure class="display-box leetcode-box">
          <Image src={leetcodeImage} alt="LeetCode profile" /> 
          <div class="action-footer">
            <a href={SOCIAL_MEDIA.LEETCODE} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="profile-btn">
              {"=> "} VIEW_LEETCODE_PROFILE
            </a>
          </div>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <section class="activity-log">
        <p>
          Yup, I've talked about my current studies, my favorite languages,
          and my obsession with LeetCode, but what do I do when I'm not
          programming? Do I play LoL like an average CS or SWE?
        </p>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <section class="activity-log">
        <p>
          I love <strong>gardening</strong>. For a
          few months now, I've been growing various veggies in my garden. My
          dad grew up in a rural area, so he knows a lot about this wonderful
          world.
        </p>

        <p>
          Actually ☝🏽🤓, that's the reason I developed a garden organizer,
          which you can (actually, it's gone, but you can take a look 
          at my other projects lol) view in the{" "}
          <a href="/projects">{SECTIONS.PROJECTS}</a> tab.
        </p>

        <p class="gardening-text">
          At the moment, I'm growing coriander, tomato, round zucchini, corn, 
          carrot, and a couple more veggies.
          In the <a href="/life">{SECTIONS.LIFE}</a> tab, you'll find some
          photos I've taken so far.
        </p>

        <figure class="display-box garden-box">
          <Image src={gardenharvest} alt="Garden harvest" />
          <figcaption>First radish harvest.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  strong {
    font-weight: bold;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  strong[data-lang="Rust"], span[data-lang="OCaml"] {
    color: var(--orange);
  }

  span[data-lang="C++"], span[data-lang="Python"], span[data-lang="C"] {
    color: var(--blue);
  }

  span[data-lang="Haskell"] {
    color: var(--purple0)
  }

  span[data-lang="Java"] {
    color: var(--red)
  }

  span[data-lang="TypeScript"], span[data-lang="Go"] {
    color: var(--cyan)
  }

  span[data-lang="Zig"] {
    color: var(--yellow)
  }

  .lang-row {
    font-family: var(--font-mono, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .lang-text {
    color: var(--fg-light);
    font-weight: bold;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .lang-text::before {
    content: "· ";
    color: var(--blue);
    margin-right: 0.25rem;
  }

  .display-box {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .display-box img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto 0.75rem;
  }

  .garden-box img {
    max-width: 400px;
  }

  .leetcode-box img {
    max-width: 550px;
  }

  figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--fg-light);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .action-footer {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .profile-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    color: var(--blue);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
  }

  .profile-btn:hover {
    background-color: var(--blue);
    color: var(--bg);
  }

  a {
    color: var(--blue);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .gardening-text {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
</style>
